          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
              <supportDesc material="paper">
                <support>Codex has dark coloured, thin oriental <material>paper</material> regular
                  chain lines. Flyleaves are thick paper with clear, readily apparent chain
                  lines.</support>
                <extent>419 folios (ii+4+419+ii) <dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                    <height>260</height>
                    <width>160</width>
                    <depth>43</depth>
                  </dimensions>
                  <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                    <height>253</height>
                    <width>154</width>
                  </dimensions>
                  <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                    <height>185</height>
                    <width>115</width>
                  </dimensions></extent>
                <foliation/>
                <collation>Binding is too tight to establish entire collation but up to folio 128 it
                  has quires of 8 leaves. Catchwords consistently provided.</collation>
                <condition>Much worm damage to the text and the book cover. The text field is clear
                  and mostly unaffected by damage. Pages have been repaired in places. Some repairs
                  in the gutter region in the last few folios of the codex.</condition>

              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout columns="1" writtenLines="19"/>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc>
              <handNote scope="major" script="naskh">Neat Indian naskh in black ink, single hand
                throughout.</handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <decoDesc>
              <decoNote>Numerous mathematical and astronomical diagrams. </decoNote>
            </decoDesc>
            <additions>Paper of the 'index' of four folios added to the codex after the flyleaves
              upside down. These additional leaves are newer, light-coloured, oriental paper with
              regular chain lines. Index folio 1 has the following written at the top of the leaf,
              which is the beginning of the index: <quote xml:lang="ar">فهرست كتاب شرح مجستي (sic)
                تصنيف عبد العلي بن محمد بن الحسين در علم هيئت معه هندسة ورق(sic).</quote> The index,
              which contains few errors, contains The number of the book and/or section followed by
              a brief description of the contents and the folio number where the section begins in
              the codex. </additions>
            <bindingDesc>
              <binding>
                <p>Oriental binding, stiff, red leather covers. On the front and back covers, there
                  are two identical unfinished gold geometric designs traced on the leather at the
                  centre of the cover. The front and back covers are outlined with gold lines with
                  small spiral patterns running along the edges. <quote xml:lang="ar">شرح
                    مجسطي</quote> (<title>Sharḥ Majisṭī</title>) is written on the top of the front
                  and back covers.</p>
              </binding>
            </bindingDesc>
          </physDesc>
